[According to the information provided by the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC), since the beginning of the 2017 transmission season and as of 27 Jul 2017, 5 human cases of West Nile fever (one confirmed and 4 probable) have been reported by Greece. In the neighbouring countries, one confirmed case and 3 probable cases have been reported; all of them were reported by Israel.

One equine case of West Nile fever has been notified through the Animal Disease Notification System (ADNS) of the European Commission. The case occurred in the Province of Rovigo, in north eastern Italy.

Additional information and a map with distribution of West Nile fever human cases by affected area are available at https://ecdc.europa.eu/en/west-nile-fever/surveillance-and-disease-data/disease-data-ecdc. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5221450,83.]
